place.name: TOFT
place.gazetteerText: TOFT, a parish in Caxton district, Cambridgeshire; 2½ miles WNW of Lords-Bridge r. station, and 6 WSW of Cambridge. Post town, Caxton, under Royston-Acres, 1,242. Real property, £1,912. Pop., 359. Houses, 79. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory, united with Caldecote, in the diocese of Ely. Value, £463.* Patron, Christ's College, Cambridge. Charities, £20. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
